I"<p>The <code>ipma</code> weather platform uses the <a href="https://www.ipma.pt/">Instituto PortuguÃªs do Mar e Atmosfera</a> as a source for current and forecast meteorological data.</p>
<h2>Configuration</h2>
<p>To add the IPMA weather platform to your installation, add the following to your <code>configuration.yaml</code> file:</p>
<pre><code class="language-yaml"># Example configuration.yaml entry
weather:
  - platform: ipma
</code></pre>
<div class="config-vars">
  <h3><a class="title-link" name="configuration-variables" href="#configuration-variables"></a> Configuration Variables</h3>
  <dl class=''><dt><a class='title-link' name='name' href='#name'></a> name</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>The name you would like to give to the weather station.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>The name of the used station</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='latitude' href='#latitude'></a> latitude</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Latitude of the location for which you want weather information.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>Home Assistant global latitude configuration</p>
</p></dd><dt><a class='title-link' name='longitude' href='#longitude'></a> longitude</dt><dd><p class='desc'><span class='type'>(<span class='string'>string</span>)</span><span class='required'>(Optional)</span><span class='description'><p>Longitude of the location for which you want weather information.</p>
</span></p><p class='default'>
Default value: <p>Home Assistant global longitude configuration</p>
</p></dd></dl>
</div>
